This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with object extraction from images using convolutional neural networks. The use of deep learning techniques also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves image processing and analysis, which could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of latent variables and optimization methods suggests that it could also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
